The paper deals with algorithms for finding optimal intervals in a sequence subject to certain constraints, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of all-pairs shortest paths suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph algorithms (cs.CC), while the optimization aspect falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
